documentation.value:
Prints to standard output with a newline.

```rust
println!("Hello, world!");
println!("x = {}", x);
println!("{name} is {age}", name="Alice", age=30);
```

Prints to standard error with a newline.

```rust
eprintln!("Error: {}", msg);
eprintln!("Warning: file not found");
```

Creates a `String` using interpolation of runtime expressions.

```rust
let s = format!("Hello, {}!", name);
let msg = format!("{} items found", count);
let addr = format!("{}:{}", host, port);
```

Creates a `Vec` containing the arguments.

```rust
let v = vec![1, 2, 3];
let zeros = vec![0; 10];
let names = vec!["Alice", "Bob"];
```

Panics the current thread with the given message.

```rust
panic!("something went wrong");
panic!("index out of bounds: {}", index);
```

Panics if the given expression is false.

```rust
assert!(x > 0);
assert!(result.is_ok(), "Expected Ok, got {:?}", result);
```

Panics if the two expressions are not equal.

```rust
assert_eq!(a, b);
assert_eq!(result, 42, "Expected 42");
```

Panics if the two expressions are equal.

```rust
assert_ne!(a, b);
assert_ne!(result, 0, "Should not be zero");
```

Indicates unfinished code. Panics with a "not yet implemented" message.

```rust
fn process() -> Result<()> {
    todo!()
}
fn handle(event: Event) {
    todo!("handle {:?}", event)
}
```

Indicates unimplemented code by panicking.

```rust
fn serialize(&self) -> Vec<u8> {
    unimplemented!()
}
```

Prints the value to stderr with file and line info and returns it.

```rust
let x = dbg!(2 + 3);
dbg!(&my_vec);
```

Writes formatted data into a buffer implementing `std::fmt::Write` or `std::io::Write`.

```rust
use std::fmt::Write;
let mut buf = String::new();
write!(buf, "Hello, {}!", name)?;
```

Same as `write!` but appends a newline.

```rust
writeln!(buf, "line: {}", i)?;
writeln!(f, "{}: {}", key, value)?;
```

Includes a UTF-8 encoded file as a string at compile time.

```rust
let contents = include_str!("data.txt");
let sql = include_str!("../migrations/001.sql");
```

Includes a file as a byte array at compile time.

```rust
let data = include_bytes!("image.png");
let cert = include_bytes!("cert.pem");
```

Concatenates literals into a `&'static str`.

```rust
let s = concat!("Hello", ", ", "world!");
let version = concat!("v", env!("CARGO_PKG_VERSION"));
```

Evaluates configuration flags at compile time and returns a bool.

```rust
if cfg!(target_os = "linux") {
    println!("Running on Linux");
}
if cfg!(debug_assertions) {
    println!("Debug mode");
}
```

Inspects an environment variable at compile time.

```rust
let version = env!("CARGO_PKG_VERSION");
let name = env!("CARGO_PKG_NAME");
```

Returns a bool indicating whether an expression matches any of the given patterns.

```rust
let is_vowel = matches!(c, 'a' | 'e' | 'i' | 'o' | 'u');
let is_some = matches!(opt, Some(_));
```

Defines a function.

```rust
fn add(a: i32, b: i32) -> i32 {
    a + b
}
fn greet(name: &str) {
    println!("Hello, {}!", name);
}
```

Creates an immutable variable binding.

```rust
let x = 5;
let name: String = String::from("Alice");
let (a, b) = (1, 2);
```

Creates a mutable variable binding.

```rust
let mut count = 0;
count += 1;
let mut buf = Vec::new();
```

Defines methods and associated functions for a type.

```rust
impl Point {
    fn new(x: f64, y: f64) -> Self {
        Self { x, y }
    }
    fn distance(&self, other: &Point) -> f64 {
        ((self.x - other.x).powi(2) + (self.y - other.y).powi(2)).sqrt()
    }
}
```

Defines a trait (interface).

```rust
trait Summary {
    fn summarize(&self) -> String;
    fn headline(&self) -> String {
        String::from("(Read more...)")
    }
}
```

Makes an item accessible from outside the current module.

```rust
pub fn public_function() {}
pub struct PublicStruct { pub field: i32 }
pub(crate) fn crate_only() {}
pub(super) fn parent_only() {}
```

Declares a module.

```rust
mod utils;
mod tests {
    use super::*;
    #[test]
    fn test_add() {
        assert_eq!(add(2, 3), 5);
    }
}
```

Brings items into scope.

```rust
use std::collections::HashMap;
use std::io::{self, Read, Write};
use crate::models::User;
```

Pattern matching on a value.

```rust
match value {
    0 => println!("zero"),
    1..=9 => println!("single digit"),
    _ => println!("other"),
}
match result {
    Ok(val) => val,
    Err(e) => return Err(e),
}
```

Combines `if` with pattern matching.

```rust
if let Some(val) = optional {
    println!("Got: {}", val);
}
if let Ok(n) = "42".parse::<i32>() {
    println!("parsed: {}", n);
}
```

Loops while a pattern matches.

```rust
while let Some(item) = stack.pop() {
    process(item);
}
while let Ok(line) = reader.read_line(&mut buf) {
    println!("{}", line);
}
```

Creates an infinite loop. Use `break` to exit.

```rust
loop {
    let input = read_input();
    if input == "quit" {
        break;
    }
    process(input);
}
let result = loop {
    if done() { break 42; }
};
```

Iterates over an iterator.

```rust
for item in &vec {
    println!("{}", item);
}
for i in 0..10 {
    println!("{}", i);
}
for (i, val) in vec.iter().enumerate() {
    println!("{}: {}", i, val);
}
```

Defines an async function that returns a `Future`.

```rust
async fn fetch(url: &str) -> Result<String, Error> {
    let resp = reqwest::get(url).await?;
    resp.text().await
}
```

Suspends execution until the future is ready.

```rust
let result = some_async_fn().await;
let body = response.text().await?;
```

Returns a value from the current function.

```rust
fn check(x: i32) -> bool {
    if x < 0 { return false; }
    true
}
```

Creates a type alias.

```rust
type Result<T> = std::result::Result<T, MyError>;
type Callback = Box<dyn Fn(i32) -> i32>;
```

Declares a compile-time constant.

```rust
const MAX_SIZE: usize = 1024;
const PI: f64 = 3.14159265358979;
```

Declares a static variable with a `'static` lifetime.

```rust
static COUNTER: AtomicUsize = AtomicUsize::new(0);
static CONFIG: &str = "default";
```

Marks a block or function as unsafe, allowing raw pointer dereferences and other unsafe operations.

```rust
unsafe {
    let val = *raw_ptr;
}
unsafe fn dangerous() { }
```

Declares an external function interface.

```rust
extern "C" {
    fn abs(input: i32) -> i32;
}
```

Specifies a trait object type with dynamic dispatch.

```rust
fn log(writer: &dyn Write) { }
let handler: Box<dyn Fn()> = Box::new(|| println!("hi"));
```

Allocates memory on the heap and places the value into it.

```rust
let b = Box::new(5);
let s = Box::new(String::from("hello"));
let trait_obj: Box<dyn Display> = Box::new(42);
```

Creates a new empty `String`.

```rust
let mut s = String::new();
s.push_str("hello");
```

Converts a `&str` into a `String`.

```rust
let s = String::from("hello");
let greeting = String::from("Hello, world!");
```

Constructs a new, empty `Vec<T>`.

```rust
let mut v: Vec<i32> = Vec::new();
v.push(1);
```

Constructs a new, empty `Vec<T>` with the specified capacity.

```rust
let mut v = Vec::with_capacity(100);
v.push(42);
assert!(v.capacity() >= 100);
```

Creates an empty `HashMap`.

```rust
use std::collections::HashMap;
let mut map = HashMap::new();
map.insert("key", "value");
```

Creates an empty `HashSet`.

```rust
use std::collections::HashSet;
let mut set = HashSet::new();
set.insert(42);
```

Creates an empty `BTreeMap` (sorted map).

```rust
use std::collections::BTreeMap;
let mut map = BTreeMap::new();
map.insert(1, "one");
```

Creates an `Option` containing a value.

```rust
let x: Option<i32> = Some(42);
let name = Some(String::from("Alice"));
```

Represents the absence of a value.

```rust
let x: Option<i32> = None;
fn find(id: u32) -> Option<&User> { None }
```

Contains the success value.

```rust
let r: Result<i32, String> = Ok(42);
fn parse(s: &str) -> Result<i32, ParseIntError> { Ok(0) }
```

Contains the error value.

```rust
let r: Result<i32, String> = Err("failed".into());
return Err(MyError::NotFound);
```

Constructs a new `Rc<T>` (single-threaded reference counting).

```rust
use std::rc::Rc;
let shared = Rc::new(vec![1, 2, 3]);
let clone = Rc::clone(&shared);
```

Constructs a new `Arc<T>` (thread-safe reference counting).

```rust
use std::sync::Arc;
let shared = Arc::new(data);
let clone = Arc::clone(&shared);
```

Creates a new `Mutex<T>`.

```rust
use std::sync::Mutex;
let m = Mutex::new(0);
let mut val = m.lock().unwrap();
*val += 1;
```

Creates a new `Cell<T>` for interior mutability of `Copy` types.

```rust
use std::cell::Cell;
let c = Cell::new(5);
c.set(10);
assert_eq!(c.get(), 10);
```

Creates a new `RefCell<T>` for interior mutability with runtime borrow checking.

```rust
use std::cell::RefCell;
let c = RefCell::new(vec![1, 2, 3]);
c.borrow_mut().push(4);
```

Automatically implements traits for a type.

```rust
#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq)]
struct Point { x: f64, y: f64 }

#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, Hash, Eq, PartialEq)]
enum Color { Red, Green, Blue }

#[derive(Default, serde::Serialize, serde::Deserialize)]
struct Config { port: u16, host: String }
```

Implements a trait for a specific type.

```rust
impl Display for Point {
    fn fmt(&self, f: &mut fmt::Formatter<'_>) -> fmt::Result {
        write!(f, "({}, {})", self.x, self.y)
    }
}
impl From<&str> for MyType {
    fn from(s: &str) -> Self { MyType(s.to_string()) }
}
```

The `?` operator propagates errors. If the value is `Err`, it returns early.

```rust
fn read_config(path: &str) -> Result<Config, Box<dyn Error>> {
    let contents = std::fs::read_to_string(path)?;
    let config: Config = serde_json::from_str(&contents)?;
    Ok(config)
}
```

Creates a closure.

```rust
let add = |a, b| a + b;
let double = |x: i32| -> i32 { x * 2 };
vec.iter().filter(|x| **x > 5).collect::<Vec<_>>();
vec.sort_by(|a, b| a.cmp(b));
```

Creates an async block.

```rust
let future = async {
    let data = fetch("http://example.com").await?;
    process(data).await
};
```

Annotates lifetimes to help the borrow checker.

```rust
fn longest<'a>(x: &'a str, y: &'a str) -> &'a str {
    if x.len() > y.len() { x } else { y }
}
struct Excerpt<'a> {
    part: &'a str,
}
```

Format trait for the `{}` marker. Used by `println!`, `format!`, etc.

```rust
